# No-op patch: the v5.6.4.2 branch HEAD compiles cleanly on the Luckfox 5.10
# BSP without modifications.
#
# Inspection of os_dep/linux/ioctl_cfg80211.c at the pinned source SHA confirms:
#   - `wiphy_ext_feature_set` is not referenced anywhere in os_dep/.
#   - `WIPHY_FLAG_HAS_REMAIN_ON_CHANNEL` is gated on
#     `LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(3, 3, 0)`, which holds on 5.10.
#   - The 5.11 / 5.19 / 6.x kernel branches are already correctly gated by
#     the upstream tree (lines 468, 483, 5326, 6202, 10498, 10500).
#
# This file is retained as a hook so that a future Luckfox BSP kernel bump
# (or a backported cfg80211 API divergence in linux-luckfox.git) can land a
# real hunk here without restructuring the recipe. Empty patches are no-ops
# in Buildroot's apply-patches.sh; the build will print one INFO line and
# continue.
